en_857892_0	Major General Jagath Gunawardena, the newly appointed 17th Colonel Commandant, Sri Lanka Engineers (SLE) assumed office during a charming ceremony, held at the SLE Headquarters on Thursday (25).
en_857892_1	He was greeted to military honours and ceremonials before a large gathering of Senior Officers, Officers and Other Ranks.
en_857892_2	The day’s Chief Guest on his arrival at the SLE Headquarters was warmly welcomed by the Centre Commandant, Brigadier Ravindra Dias and accorded a Guard Turnout.
en_857892_3	Afterwards, the visiting Colonel Commandant laid a floral wreath at the War Heroes’ monument to pay his tribute to all those who made the supreme sacrifice in defence of the country.
en_857892_4	A few minutes later, a parade saluted him in the parade ground.
en_857892_5	Thereafter, Major General Jagath Gunawardena signed an official document to signify the acceptance of the new office as the new Colonel Commandant amidst chanting of ‘Seth Pirith’ by members of the Maha Sangha.
en_857892_6	Major General Jagath Gunawardena afterwards had a formal meeting with Senior Officers and attended refreshments with All Ranks at the Convention Centre.
en_857892_7	As the next event of the day’s ceremony, Colonel Commandant addressed All Ranks and spoke out his mind and the future vision for the SLE.
en_857892_8	Afterwards, the Colonel Commandant had a meeting with all Commanding Officers and Regimental Sergeant Majors and received an update on the role and tasks of different formations.
en_857892_9	A large gathering of Officers were present during the proceedings.
en_857892_10	Major General Jagath Gunawardena, is presently performing duties as the Commander Security Forces - Wanni.
